Member Enumeration Documentation

enum FilteredGfxMapRequest::state_t [protected]
 

Describes what we should be doing right now.

Enumeration values:
USING_GFX_REQUEST  Means that we are currently using the GfxFeatureMapRequest.
GENERIC_STATE  Means that we are using this request.
ERROR  The request is done, but with an error.
DONE_OK  The request is done and ok.

Creates a new FilteredGfxMapRequest which is inside another request.

Parameters:
requestOrID Id of the request or the parent request. Automatically converts from uint16 or Request*.
redLineSettings Settings for the red line in java client.
mapDesc A reference to the tilemapformatdesc.
bbox The boundingbox of the resulting gfxmap.
tileMapLayerID Tilemap layer id, (map, route, poi:s etc).
tileMapImportanceNbr Tilemap importance nbr. This determines which features that will be kept in the resulting map.
pixelToMeter Pixel to meter factor.
routeReplyPack The route replypacket. May be NULL if the route layer is not included.
topReq Pointer to valid TopRegionRequest with data
removeNames If to skip the names of the gfxmap.
resultMap If the result should be a gfxmap or tilemap.
rights the map rights for pois
